President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Patricia Neuman for multiple positions related to healthcare. Neuman, currently a senior vice president at the Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation, will be nominated to serve as a member of the Supplementary Medical Insurance Trust Fund Board of Trustees, the Federal Hospital Insurance Trust Fund Board of Trustees, and the Federal Old-Age and Survivors Insurance Trust Fund and the Federal Disability Insurance Board of Trustees. Neuman is a recognized expert in Medicare policy and has extensive knowledge of issues related to coverage, affordability, spending and financing, care for older Americans and people with disabilities, and proposals to sustain Medicare for the future. She has testified before Congressional committees and has published extensively on health coverage and retirement security. Neuman has previous experience working in the House of Representatives and the U.S. Senate Special Committee on Aging. She holds a doctorate in health policy and management and a masters in health finance and management from Johns Hopkins University.